data.text:
This is an original 1871 black and white wood engraving of Fredrick Francis II, the German Grand Duke of Mecklenburg-Schwerin during the Franco-Prussian War that lasted between 1870-1871 CE.

CONDITION

This 140+ year old Item is rated Very Fine +++. Light aging throughout. No creases. No natural defects.No surface rub.No tears. No water damage.

Product Type: Original Wood Engraving; Black / White

Grade: Very Fine +++

Dimensions: Approximately 4.5 x 5.5 inches; 11 x 14 cm

Authentication: Serial-Numbered Certificate of Authenticity w/ Full Provenance

Protection: Packaged in a custom archival sleeve with an acid-free black board (great for display, gift-giving, and preservation)

Join Period Paper in the cause of perusing a portfolio of images portraying the battlefield glories of the Franco-Prussian War. March with German Field Marshal, Otto Von Bismarck, as he seeks to unify the nation of Germany under the staunch leadership of Kaiser Wilhelm I. Allow your interest to be captured along with Napoleon III, the last Emperor of France, whose imprisonment sparked the fires of another French Revolution. See the political masterminds behind the Paris Commune of 1871 and apply cutting edge military tactics of carrier pigeon couriers and duck pacification. To continue browsing these images, simply click the link provided below the condition paragraph. Enjoy!

Keywords specific to this image: Franco Prussian War, Franco German War, Uniform, Commander, General, Politician, Government, Russian General Field Marshal
